N:scrapling
D:[scrapling] Install, configure, and operate Scrapling for adaptive web scraping with parser-first HTML extraction, fast HTTP fetchers, browser rendering, stealth anti-bot options, CLI extraction, and optional MCP or spider workflows.
G:scrapling web-scraping crawling adaptive-scraping mcp cli playwright cloudflare spiders python

U[8]:
  Install Scrapling with parser-only or extras-based profiles and download browser dependencies when needed
  Start with Selector for known HTML and choose Fetcher DynamicFetcher or StealthyFetcher only when live fetching is required
  Reuse session classes for repeated requests instead of one-off browser launches
  Parse with CSS, XPath, ::text, ::attr, text search, regex, and similar-element lookup
  Enable adaptive scraping with adaptive=True, auto_save=True, retrieve, and relocate
  Use the CLI for get post put delete fetch stealthy-fetch and shell prototyping
  Treat MCP and spiders as secondary workflows once parser and fetcher behavior is proven
  Build Scrapy-like spiders with concurrency follow links and pause or resume checkpoints when crawl scope expands

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Install,bash scripts/install.sh --profile parser|fetchers|shell|ai|all and run browser install only when needed
  2,Parse first,use Selector for local HTML and known DOM extraction before escalating to live fetchers
  3,Choose fetcher,start with Fetcher then escalate to DynamicFetcher or StealthyFetcher only on JS or protection needs
  4,Parse and adapt,use Response and Selector APIs with CSS XPath text regex and adaptive matching
  5,Prototype,run bash scripts/run-extract.sh and scrapling shell for quick checks
  6,Extend,use bash scripts/run-mcp.sh or Spider Request Response only when the task grows beyond normal extraction

R[8]:
  Prefer Selector or the lightest fetcher that works and escalate only on real rendering or protection needs
  Session classes are better than repeated one-off fetches for multi-page jobs
  Adaptive scraping is opt-in and should be enabled only where selector brittleness matters
  Use CSS selectors and markdown or text output to reduce token and storage overhead
  Browser-backed features require extras plus scrapling install to download Playwright or Patchright dependencies
  Scrapling is documented for HTML parsing and does not currently focus on XML feeds
  MCP stdio is the simplest local integration; add --http only when you need streamable HTTP
  Respect target authorization boundaries robots terms and rate limits

E[6]{type,command}:
  Install,bash scripts/install.sh
  Static CLI,bash scripts/run-extract.sh get "https://example.com" content.md --css-selector "article"
  Dynamic CLI,bash scripts/run-extract.sh fetch "https://app.example.com" content.md --network-idle
  Stealth CLI,bash scripts/run-extract.sh stealth "https://protected.example.com" content.md --solve-cloudflare
  MCP,bash scripts/run-mcp.sh --http --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
  Spider,python your_spider.py
